    "summary": "I am a landscape ecologist with 10 years of research and work experience in Guatemala, Brazil, and Europe. I have recently completed my joint PhD on land use planning and resource ecology between SupAgro Montpellier and Wageningen University & Research.\n\nMy research and professional interests lie at the intersection of landscape ecology and land change science for policy and technical advice concerning agricultural and food system transitions. I am also interested in critical environmental humanities and the intellectual history of the notion of nature. I believe inter and transdisciplinary approaches will be fundamental to reinvent human-nature interactions and address systemic challenges in upcoming decades.",
